<Selected><T>Bool</T><D>0</D></Selected>
<Text>&lt;P class=MsoTitle style=&quot;BORDER-TOP: medium none; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 0.75pt solid; PADDING-BOTTOM: 1pt; PADDING-TOP: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in&quot; align=center&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT size=5 face=Arial&gt;Final Lab&amp;nbsp;Template&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: center; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&quot; align=center&gt;&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This template is a simple example of a Data Flow workspace that can be used for DPD Extraction and validation.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The &quot;DPD Extraction&quot;&amp;nbsp;schematic is used to obtain input and output&amp;nbsp;signals of PA, and stores them&amp;nbsp;in files. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#404040 size=2&gt;The&amp;nbsp;files store the signals&amp;nbsp;can be used in Matlab to extract the DPD models. Of course, you can also extract models&amp;nbsp;in SystemVue, as&amp;nbsp;we did in the previous Lab, which&amp;nbsp;are suitable for some simpler methods ,such as MP model.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The &quot;DPD Validation&quot;&amp;nbsp;schematic is used to validate the DPD performance. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;In Matlab script of&amp;nbsp; &quot;DPD Validation&quot;&amp;nbsp;schematic , three methods are preset, among which &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#404040&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Method = 1 corresponds to &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;FeedForwardNet, &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#404040 size=2&gt;Method = 2 corresponds to Regression &lt;FONT size=2&gt;Learner App&lt;/FONT&gt;, &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#404040 size=2&gt;Method = 3&amp;nbsp;corresponds to Deep Network Designer. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;More details are in &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Final_Lab_example.m&lt;/FONT&gt; and &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Supplementary Information for Final Lab.pdf&lt;/FONT&gt;.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#x000D;&#x000A;&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Of course, you can use your &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;own method&lt;/FONT&gt; by &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;r&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;ewriting codes&lt;/FONT&gt;.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;</Text>
